content: Today we will continue analysing the WC games.
before we heat up the brains, lets make fingers warm.
Last time we analysed 3 of my games from last WC.

slamduk, yzhnie, Iskander, dreamy, pzh, Ikon, xuwu, MIMI, blueice, skywalker, oddgod, Lianzhuxuetu, ouyang, benben, lkogr, okabe, hobbang, derkas, yun_shou, voshkod, cy, weigui, xiaoxin, whywhy, shuwang, yysanyue, sunrain, mima, yyfcsd, farmer, Liuchao, Whiz.
The last one was the draw game with Artemiev.
He didn't want to fight either,
Other than that, Artemiev has become a good player,
you may all remember him from renjuclass, by name ASV777.
When he came to renjuclass, he was beginner of renju.
Later on he met other renju players from his city,
and started to play renju live as well.
Now he is strong AT player.
That is an example for you that anyone of you may be successful.
by the way, about advanced homework last week:
I thought the most dangerous Russian player would be Artemiev the AT
was this black win or not? :)
those who declared it as black win  and proved it, got right answer.
As you know, in previous round there were 2 games of this variant -
my game with chingin and tarannikov vs andersson.
There Andersson played there and got very good position later.
However, the difference between 3rd and 4th round was perhaps 2 hours.
I did not have time to analyse this 34th move.
It is too risky move to play it without proper analysis.
So I had no choice but to play another move here.
Here, I tried to improve white's tactics a bit.
to not let black take e13 space.
in game with chingin, black had too strong space above,
so it was difficult for white to run to the right wing with tempo.
but now, black doesnt get the space power.
and i was able to attack first.
what would you do here as white?
haha, you would have to put a stone anyway
in such case, black wins tempo
and on 5th round, I  played with him.
its ok, suhkov had 0 from 2, but was leader by 4 from 6 later.
I had prepared myself all night,
I have  played only a few games by this variant.
This looks like optimal sequence for both sides.
There have been quite many games by this variant.
And its surprising that there are so many different ways to continue.
Before our game it was still unclear,
is it better for black or white. Hard to say.
A game in QT was 19-h5 and white won
Usually, more experienced player would win here with any color :P
we have seen moves like this
I expected a defense move here,
but he played very actively and fast,
When I looked at it, it really looked scary.
I could not see any attack chance for white at first look.
So I started to think about what black could do here.
I came to conclusion that if I let black attack, I would lose the game.
So I needed the miracle, to save white.
I spent so much time here.
The next move for white is logical.
But from here, hard to find the right move.
many moves seem to create a vcf threat.
is this move a vcf threat?
this is class, not TV, dear students
But what can black do here
good, we have 2 offers. any other?

Samsone, Ikon, chess, cy, MIMI, pzh, yzhnie, derkas, hobbang, lkogr, SamSite, whywhy, dreamy, yyfcsd, oddgod, benben, xiaoxin, skywalker, ouyang, Lianzhuxuetu, farmer, weigui, Liuchao, Whiz, mima, Iskander, shuwang, okabe, coco_yuang, yysanyue, xuwu, voshkod, xiaoxiaohua, sunrain, xinxin.
think as if it was your own game
and you had to find defense as black
i will wait until i get suggestions from at least 15 students
I think k8 then i3 and h4
Majority thinks k8. lets do it then.
does white have vcf threat now?
it seems white has an advantage now
perhaps m8 was not best move?
guest500, some minutes ago we showed white vcf on k6
why? there are so many possible moves for black.
pzh, if you mention 4, then please tell next move too
Think this way - there are many moves that can defend against white win here.
but we need to find the one which doesnt let white attack below and ruin black powers below
yes, hard to choose the right one
can white continue attack in any way?
maybe you have other ways here than vcf
next question from here: does black have vcf?
here are 36 students in room, but only 1/3 is really paying attention to lesson
I tought J8 without k8 was better
we will try that as next
After today's lesson, all passive names will be removed from today's cp list.
We found lots of interesting attacks.
28-L10 in real game would have been troublesome for both players :)
In the game, I found sure win move.
So after this 28, black cannot attack.
But its also hard to defend.
because white would be too strong.
so he played the only hope move
I saw you put 36 and 38 strongly :)
who can show white win? say me
And this game finished first in 5th round
this 44 is very hard to think
That was a happy game for me,
and gave me leadership in tournament.
But the next game, was a tragedy for me.
Before the AT I had made a plan,
to not lose any games in AT.
Draw was acceptable, but no losses.
Stefan Karlsson surprised me by playing this opening in 6th round.
I wanted to create something new here,
to make this "draw" variant to become "win" variant.
So I resolved this lower area with new method.
Finally he placed the strongest move.
the vertical e-line is the new tactics for black
He keeps defending with best moves.
I thought about 1 hour and 30 minutes for next move
Didn't he spend more than an hour in 34?
so for 3 moves, we spent about 3-4 hours
So many black moves seemed nearly win.
You know, the time rule was.. after you put a stone on board, you get another 30 seconds to clock
The idea was to take the lower corner force,
and develop into winning attack on right side.
L9 is key point for black.
If black reaches there, black wins easily.
Strong opponent Karlsson of course found correct 40.
He had played series of only possible moves, starting from 32.
else white can counterattack from d3.
Now I had 30 seconds left on clock.
And he found best defense again.
And here, my time was running towards 0, I had to find win.
There are at least 2 ways to win.
If no one, I will try...
I had to decide between 2 attack startings
but here is a cut move?
so, time was ticking.. 10,9,8... on clock..
i had to decide... how to begin.
but after writing down the move,
and looking on board, the time was still too few..
and then i had to throw a stone, to avoid loss, and immediately hit clocks.
but for my unlucky, i missed the spot.
On the board, there are 173 draw spots.
in 1 second, i was able to find the loss spot
so, my sure win became sure loss in 1 second.
but next day, when i analysed the game with mr yamaguchi,
he said, only a strong master can find the loss move in 1 second.
most players need maybe 1 hour to find where is loss move, exvept for i2
that must have been a comforting phrase
hahaha, i was so angry to myself,
this loss move is very hard to  find  :)
for not keeping enough safe time on clock.
so i spent much time on 35.
so that my new theory of 29 could be a glorious example
if Stefan played so many "only" moves, can you consider 29+31 to be black win ? :)
sometimes it takes a "sacrifice" to prove a new win method.
He means, even though it was tragic for me,
I have not had time to analyse all.
But this game was better tactics for black than any other development in the past
yes, most blacks sacrifice lower part totally and try the left side
this move is also a question
because now D6 is open attack for black
maybe this game proved black win in i11
but he had some reasons in it
So, most innovative and beautiful game turned to be my only loss game in AT.
The lesson is over, Thank you all.
it would've been too perfect, if won
